Description: 878 Sq. Ft. BACK HOUSE!  Charming home on a quiet street in Terrell Hills.  Step into an open foyer that welcomes you to the large living room with a cozy fireplace. A Dining room full of windows has a swinging butlers door leading you into the stylish and functional kitchen. This beautiful kitchen includes 2 pantries, stainless appliances, wolf range, built in oven, quartz countertops. The kitchen  overlooks an oasis of a back yard and a cozy family room.  The Master suite has a gorgeous rock wall with a fireplace. The Master Bath offers a double vanity, walk in closet and large glass shower.  Carrera Marble floors makes for a luxury master bath.  The spacious second Master with an ensuite bath, along with the secondary bedrooms and full size bath, all located on the main floor. The family room, accented with skylights, a shiplap panelled accent wall with a wet bar and built in wine fridge. The large utility/laundry/mud room has ample storage and leads you to a breezeway connecting you to the enclosed garage and Casita. The garage was closed in with a floating wall so it can easily be converted back. It features stained concrete floors, a mini split for heating and cooling along with a 16x10 walk in closet with built in shelving. Access the Casita through the garage or off of the deck in the backyard. The Casita consists of a full kitchen and bath along with a step down room with two closets. The heated pool and hot tub can be enjoyed year-round. The large backyard also includes a storage shed, playscape, fireplace and partially covered deck/patio with plenty of room for entertaining. Numerous parking spaces in the front and rear, including a carport.

This charming completely renovated 1930's Houston Heights bungalow has moved to Hempstead! Amazing curb appeal with well-manicured yard & welcoming covered porch complete w/ceiling fan. Feel nostalgic with details such as wide baseboards & fully trimmed windows yet modern with the shiplap sliding barn door. The dining room is huge & can accommodate a large table & any size crowd. Original details such as a built-in china cabinet & shiplap wood walls are featured. Adjacent is the kitchen completely updated w/stainless appliances, new cabinets, & quartz counters. The primary bedroom features a private bath, stained glass windows, & natural wood shiplap wall. Two more roomy bedrooms, another full bath, & a fabulous utility/mudroom complete this home. Updates include roof, HVAC, plumbing, paint, wiring, siding, windows & light fixtures.

Welcome to this fully renovated 4 bedroom, 3 bathroom home just a few blocks away from Galveston beach. This beauty stands out from the moment you drive by. Completely updated/remodeled inside and outside,this one story,3 bedrooms,2 baths property is located in desirable north side Briarmeadow subdivision.With tons of natural light and open floor plan,the property has new waterproof laminate flooring in all living areas with new shiplap accent wall with fireplace in the living room, new fixtures throughout the home,and interior fresh paint.Chef's kitchen is fully remodeled with new soft closing craftmaid cabinets with custom storage shelving,quartz countertops,and subway tile backsplash.Stay organized with extra storage in the laundry/mudroom.New carpets and padding in all the bedrooms, and all bathrooms are updated.Primary suite is fully remodeled w/ barn door.Updated primary bath including new shower, tile, cabinets, sink, fixtures. Horse lovers dream! 40 acre horse ranch located north of Paris, Texas on hard surface FM road. Shiplap walls and hard wood flooring welcome you to the cozy 1920's farmhouse, restored to perfection. Open living area, kitchen, dining, 2 bedroom suites and a bonus room. 2160sf horse barn features 6 12x12 stalls (1 converts to foaling stall) with fans for each stall, tack room, feed room, office, bathroom and wash bay. 3 sides offer screen doors. South and North doors allow for drive-thru .Concrete floor, electric and water. 15' overhang for storing hay or watching the action on the sandy soil riding arena. Round pen, loafing sheds, shop and 2 new ponds, fenced paddock areas and hay meadow complete the property.

This stunning home is nestled in the Westridge Addition and is definitely one of Plainview's finest homes. From the beautiful stucco exterior to the Spanish tile roof, hand placed stone in driveways, side patio and back yard, no expense was spared on this beauty. You won't want to leave home with all of its amenities.  It features 6 bedrooms, 3.5 baths and 3 car garage. It is open concept from kitchen to living area. This home has abundant storage throughout. The isolated master suite is a great retreat with its own sitting area, fireplace and master bath with the ultimate walk-in closet. All bedrooms have large walk-in closets. (See Supplement for More Details) The kitchen is a chef's dream come true. It includes a separate Sub-Zero refrigerator and freezer and an extra-large island as well as state-of-the-art features and appliances. The media style basement is oversized and makes a perfect getaway for movie night. This home features hardwood floors throughout as well as crown molding, plantation shutters and many windows overlooking the beautiful well maintained yard. From the sunroom you will enter into outdoor living at its best!! If you like to entertain, this home is for you! An oversized patio features a complete outdoor kitchen, fireplace, hot tub and outdoor restroom, swimming pool, pergola and storage building. The property is surrounded by an 8 ft. privacy fence and security system/cameras throughout. This home has so many more features that can only be found with a personal tour for that perfect buyer!

A FEW MORE DETAILS:
Just past the beautiful wood double doors you will be in the entry welcoming you to the office area on the left and the dining area on the right. Multiple size windows will be abundant in just about every room in this house. There are coffered ceilings, crown molding, artistically colored walls, plantation shutters and solid doors and real wood floors. 

The comfortable sized living room will have you in awe as you see the hanging ring light fixture and beautiful fireplace flanked with built-ins. The 10 ft. ceilings here will enhance the built-in surround sound system. 

The kitchen is perfectly adjacent and open to the living room area. The oversized marble top island utilizes all space with enclosed underneath storage. Remodeled within the past four years, this amazing kitchen features a Bosch dishwasher, commercial grade oven and separate built-in refrigerator and freezer. The beautiful cabinetry is all designed with extra hidden lighting. There is a small pantry, as well as a larger one for your convenience. 

This home is perfect for the family, however, after a great day together, you will love your isolated master retreat. Very spacious, the bedroom provides a small sitting area near the very pretty stucco fireplace. Continuing through to the master bath, you will have two walk-in closets that the lady of the house will just love because aside from the wardrobe areas, there are separate shoe closets and a very nice area for jewelry and personal items. 

The amazing master bath has a double vanity, large Jacuzzi style tub and a walk-in shower with THREE shower heads! The towel warmers will just make your day! 

Each of the other five bedrooms in this home have walk-in closets, ceiling fans and recessed lighting. One will also have a window seat with storage space. There will be three full baths, as well as a powder room/half bath. 

Think you need more storage space? Well, there is more in the hall closet at the top of the carpeted stairs guiding you to the full size basement complete with, yes, more storage space! The basement is currently designed as a media room. 

The mud room/utility area features Travertine tile, a sink, more storage space and a coat closet. Just off this area is the triple car garage, which also has additional washer/dryer connections. 

In the impressive, enclosed sunroom you will find more Travertine tile, three skylights and a wall of windows for a perfect view of the back patio. The complete wet bar is on one end of the sunroom and spacious enough for all your entertaining glassware and beverages. 

Now that you have a beautiful home for your family indoors, it's time to check out the amazing outdoor area! Stepping out of your sunroom you will walk into a beautiful, covered patio complete with a full size stone gas fireplace, two televisions, full kitchen, bar, in-ground hot tub with a lounger, five seats and a remote for controlling your preferences. 

When we say "full size" kitchen we mean there is a commercial flat grill with two gas burners, fridge, barbecue grill, built-in trash cans, cabinets and the bar area large enough to seat 8-10 persons. 

If this entertaining area isn't quite enough for you, maybe the full size in-ground pool will seal the deal. The 16'x36' pool has a Bahama ledge and is 8 foot at its deepest. The heated saltwater pool has a small rock wall with waterfall on one side and water sprayers on the other. Built-in stone benches serve as a resting area for pool watchers. The retractable cover will keep it secure when not in use. 

An outdoor half bath, nicely designed with shiplap will keep swimmers from having to go inside the house. 

Just past the pool area you will find another wonderful area for "me time". A beautiful pergola, built just three years ago, is wired for electricity and ceiling fans. A storage building with cinder block interior sits at the end of the yard for all your outdoor essentials. A side yard located just away from all the beauty in this back yard is where you will find the mechanicals that keep it all running smoothly. 

Along the 8 ft. fence surrounding the backyard is just enough space for your favorite florals and greenery. 

Completing the outdoors of this amazing home is beautiful Spanish tile roof, imported directly from Spain, as well as real copper gutters. There are eight outdoor cameras and plenty of outdoor lighting for that extra security. 

The front circle drive is accentuated with the lush grass area, an array of mature trees, large boulders and the perfect mailbox topped with the same Spanish tile as the house. 

There is so much more to this home that can only be found with a tour for the perfect buyer.
